Description: Linux-native meeting transcription and summarization service
 Vox Daemon is a background service that captures video call audio via
 PipeWire, transcribes it with Whisper (GPU-accelerated), performs speaker
 diarization, and generates AI-powered post-call summaries.
 .
 Features:
  - PipeWire-native audio capture
  - Local Whisper transcription (GPU-accelerated)
  - Speaker separation (mic vs. remote audio)
  - AI-powered meeting summaries (Ollama, OpenAI-compatible)
  - System tray control with desktop notifications
  - Markdown and JSON export
